# 📘 Array Scripts Overview

This file explains the idea behind **three array operations**:

---

## 🔹 1. Using `for` Loop
➡️ Iterates through the array step by step using an index. Best when you clearly know the start and end.
![alt text](images/image-34.png)
---

## 🔹 2. Using `while` Loop + Length
➡️ Uses a counter variable along with the array’s length to move through elements until the condition fails.
![alt text](images/image-32.png)
---

## 🔹 3. Array Slicing
➡️ Extracts a specific portion of the array based on given start and end positions, without changing the original array.
![alt text](images/image-33.png)